  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Textbooks Printing and Distribution II</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(Afghanistan):  The Ministry of Education (MoE) relies entirely upon donor support to print and deliver textbooks to schools across Afghanistan. Textbook Printing and Distribution II (Textbooks II) is a five-year activity to print and distribute textbooks for students in grades 1-12. The Textbooks II activity will use a Government to Government (G2G) mechanism to print and distribute more than 135 million textbooks for all students in grades 1-12. Printing companies will deliver the textbooks directly to provincial education departments (PEDs) to avoid delay in the distribution of textbooks from the MoE to PEDs. With FY 2018 funds, USAID, through the MoE, will print 49 million textbooks and teachers&apos; guides and distribute them to all 34 provinces of Afghanistan. This will enable students to have all the required textbooks. This activity will contribute to the Integrated Strategy objective to promote inclusive growth by providing students with the textbooks they need to achieve better learning outcomes..</narrative>
  </description>
